{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Revoke rules against accusing MPs of deliberate falsehoods in House of Commons",
        "additional_details": "They made sense in the days when it was unthinkable that Members would deliberately mislead the House, and historically served to guard against inappropriate hyperbole. \r\n\r\nThese rules serve no purpose in today's House, and are not appropriate today, in a time when certain Members are felt by many to have misled the House time and time again.\r\n\r\nIt makes a mockery of British democracy, for one MP who uses the term \"liar\" to be sanctioned, while no action is taken against another to whom many feel the term accurately applies.",
        "background": "The rules that prohibit MPs from accusing other MPs of committing \u2018deliberate falsehoods\u2019 in the House of Commons are an anachronism. ",
